<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Chosen-Modality</title>
  <!--[if lt IE 9]>
    <script src="http://html5shim.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/html5.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
  <![endif]-->
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag    "application", :media => "all" %>
  <%= javascript_include_tag "application" %>
  <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
</head>
<body>

  <div class="navbar navbar-fixed-top">
    <div class="navbar-inner">
      <div class="container">
        <a class="btn btn-navbar" data-toggle="collapse" data-target=".nav-collapse">
          <span class="icon-bar"></span>
          <span class="icon-bar"></span>
          <span class="icon-bar"></span>
        </a>
        <a class="brand" href="#">Chosen-Modality</a>
        <div class="nav-collapse">
          <ul class="nav">
            <li><%= link_to "Practitioners", practitioners_path %></li>
            <li><%= link_to "Modalities", modalities_path %></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

<div class="container">

  <div class="container">
    <% flash.each do |name, msg| %>
      <div class="alert alert-<%= name == :notice ? "success" : "error" %>">
        <a class="close" data-dismiss="alert">x</a>
        <%= msg  %>
      </div>
    <% end %>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="span10"><%= yield %></div>
    <div class="span2">
      <h1>helpful hints</h1>
        <p>
          This is a demonstration of two different styles of multiple selection of an associated model: <b>Modality</b>. If your desired choice is not on the list, you may add it.
        </p>
        <p>
          In the <em>Old Manual Method</em>, only one new choice may be added. With the <em>New Chosen Method</em>, you may add as many new choices as you like.
        </p>
        <hr/>
        <p>
          Courgette greater plantain. Yam swiss chard spring onion arracacha, plectranthus fiddlehead ricebean lima bean dandelion.
        </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

</body>
</html>
